surveys.narrative: WHITE SUCKERS WERE FOUND AT BELOW LOCAL MEDIAN NUMBERS. BOWFIN, LARGEMOUTH BASS, GREEN SUNFISH, AND PUMPKINSEED WERE SAMPLED NEAR THE MEDIAN. CARP BLACK BULLHEAD, YELLOW BULLHEAD, NORTHERN PIKE, YELLOW PERCH, BLUEGILL, BLACK CRAPPIE, AND HYBRID SUNFISH WERE SAMPLED AT ABOVE LOCAL MEDIAN LEVELS. BULLHEADS DOMINATE THE POPULATION. LOCAL REPORTS INDICATE THAT RICE LAKE IS A FREQUENT WINTERKILL LAKE. IT IS SUSPECTED THAT GAMEFISH MAY ENTER RICE LAKE FROM FISHLAKE AND INCREASE IN ABUNDANCE IN PERIODS BETWEEN KILLS.

BLB were the only spec. tkn in num. abv meds. YB, PS, Blgl, and BLC were tkn in nums. blw the local med. YP were above the local med. trap net and N Pike were below the local med. BLB are the only species of fish found in significant numbers. Lcl reports and this fact indicate that Rice Lk is a Chrnc wntrkl lk. Both bluegills and black crappies were found in above average numbers. Each species had an average weight of approximately 1/4 of a pound. The northern pike population is also high. The average weight and length are 2.6 pounds and 21.6 inches. Twenty five percent of the northern pike sampled were longer than twenty five inches. The black bullhead population has dropped significantly since the 1985 survey. In 1994 alone, commercial fisherman removed 9380 pounds of bullheads. Largemouth bass, while sampled in small numbers, were abundant for this type of lake. Their average length, however, was only 8.3 inches. Rice Lake also contains a large population of yellow perch. A majority of these fish are in the seven to eight inch range.
